Table.SCRIPT: There’s a city in [{southern}] Alaska called Anchorage. It is a unique place because [{moose}] live in the city at different times of the year. The moose live in Anchorage because they feel [{comfortable}] there. In the wild, bears try to kill and eat moose. In the city, there is [{plenty}] of food to eat. Moose and other animals get food from [{dumpsters}]. They also eat [{branches}] from the trees or plants from people’s gardens. People don’t [{mind}] the moose, and they have even made the animal a symbol of the city.
Table.TITLE: City Animals
